Text: What in the hells!? How'd they get past the gates!?

Remember the towers!
Remember the Reach!
Nooo! Begone! Leave my mind be!

Gods, a chimera!
A very large chimera!

This fight is yours!
You've all but won!

Out of your beds, soft ones!
TonightTodayTodayTonight, you perish by my blade!

Hand over your treasures now
and I'll make certain the cut
is clean and your deaths quick.

There it was again. Like me
da on the privy after a
plate o' dragon peppers!

Third line! Take them
from the rear!

That'll learn 'em to
cross the Confederacy!

The day is yours...but
mark my word, we will return.

Turnips and beets,
oh, so sweet!

Hearts and livers,
send me shivers!

<sniff> <sniff>
The season... It is upon us... <cough>

Hah hah hah!
You've shown those officers why we still call them petty!
But they are my officers, and I wouldn't be their commander if I didn't defend their honor to the last.
To arms, men! Let us show them what for!

A basket full!
A full basket!

Take them away!
Take them far, far away!
My fish... My tasty, tasty fish...

Gone, gone, gone!
The koja have all gone!♪

They tried to harry me
But now I'm going home♪

With fish in my basket and
a heart filled with song!♪

You there! Yeah you,
the ugly one!

I've a sack o' coin here
with yer name on it!

None o' them unsightly knobs,
now. Only the beauteous ones.

I's thinkin' I have
more'n enough...thanks to ye.

Bleedin' blighted bollocks!
That'll learn me to trust a
'venturer.

Impressive. You say
she'she's an adventurer?

High time I headed back,
I reckon.

Thank you kindly, miladymilord.
I'll learn the plow, just like
my da wanted. Promise!
Intruders!? How did they get in!?

Whatever it is, it appears
to be in ill repair.

Do you think it safe
to approach?

Absolutely not! Gods know
what manner of traps the
enemy planted upon it!

But perhaps there are
parts worth salvaging.

That can wait. We must
first report this to camp.

Rhalgr take us all! What in
the seven hells did you do!?

You just got us killed!
Come on! We have to
find cover!

M-M-Might I humbly suggest
those boulders yonder?

It was true...
It was all true!

Trust... Forgiveness...
They are truly what bind us.

I should have
been a carpenter!

For too long have I
suffered the likes of man!
You will pay! All of you!

I heard shouting.
Am I too late?

The day would not have
been won without your aid.

Never before have I
seen such a display!

Are you certain
they are all dead?

Not sure I likes me
the look of that griffin.

Times like this, I wish I'd
turned adventurer...

Don't you wander too far with
them feathers.

I've still coin, if you've
still feathers!

Look behind every bush,
every rock, every stable.

Even the slightest rustle of
the leaves could be an enemy
in waiting.

Peace walk with you, traveler.
What brings your tribe down
from yon peaks?

Peace? We left peace lying
in a ditch two days back.

If it is warmth you seek, our
fires are yours. If it is shelter,
our caves are yours.

And what of your food!?
Your gold!? Your furs!?

We have naught but that
which we carry on our backs.

Then we shall
take your backs!

You will not find
them easily given.

This one will
make a fine slave!

I am one with the steppe,
the steppe is one with me.

Come, boys! There are
slaves enough for all of us!
They are weak! We are strong!

We still have our backs.
The same cannot be said
of you and yours.

Gather the survivors! Tonight
we are the kings of the steppe!
Because one of me is never enough!
Whoa, there! I thought we were friends!?
I wouldn't look too close if I were you!

It is as I said. The prey here
is plentiful. But do not forget
we walk on Oroniri soil.

The steppe belongs to
no man! We hunt where
we please!
Then you die where we please!

You will stay off our lands
or your children will meet
the same grim fate!

We will find you! And leave
your bones for the beetles!

Mimiroon will show!
Mimiroon will lead!

Bellies abursting with
beets and broccoli!

Tummies atumbling with
turnips and tomatoes!

If I am to survive this day
I will need a boon from the
heavens...
Back to the dark with you!

He looks of breakfast,
lunch, brunch, and dinner!

I can feel their
beady little eyes!
Now that wasn't very smart, was it?
Fall back! They are too many!

They have not seen
the last of us!

My thanks! You are welcome
to as much meat as you can
carry!

The legend lives
to see another sun...

Send them back
over the Chain!

I call on your winds...
The rains which nourish...
I shall tend to your wounds.

I told you not to
start without me!

Ancient rock awaken!
Grant thy strength unto me!

And into this vessel
I bind thee for eternity!

O, giver of life and bringer
of the morn! What am I to do?

The dark seeks to claim
my only light─my dzo!

Mighty Azim, grant this
traveler strength!

Praise the sun!
My charge is safe!
The stench! It must be stifled!
Keep it back from the village!

<inhale>
The air is clean once again!

My people are in danger!
I must warn them!

Most hastily we must
make our haste!

Mimiroon is man of peace!
Mimiroon cannot bear
these bluntest of thumpings!

So afraid is poor Mimiroon.
What will befall poor Mimiroon?

Mimiroon did not think
such plan would work!

Come, hungriest of hungries!
Our banquet is here!
I see you made quick work of these green recruits.

Now do you understand why
I tell you to never leave the
village on your own?

Alright... But next time,
let's go together.

I just wanted to take
Papa some flowers.

Tonight we eat
and eat and eat!

To the bonfire!
To the bonfire!

No meat is there
on these here bones!
All gristle and grime, I am!
Though I'd be disappointed with aught less from the bloody hero of the realm!
But what say we toss you a bone with a deal more meat on her? Officers! Form ranks!
Traveler. Please, I beg of you!

I don't like being followed.
Name yourself!
My tribe will not forgive this...

These are the men who
worked their treachery on me!

The damned this is tracking
us... It knows we are here!

Wait. If this machine can track
us, then fleeing back to camp...

Would lead the enemy
right where it wants to go!
But if we can't go back...

I've a feeling “hide here
until help arrives” is out
of the question.

As of the moment, that's
about all I had...

Looks as if we're
out of boulders.

We will prevail...
We will prevail...

There is much we can
learn from today's defeat.

It will be moons before these
men and women are ready.

Carry the wounded
to the barbers' tents!

Meat-loving minions!
Meat-loving minions...?
No more minions, eh?

Then Mimiroon shall meet
the meat we beat to eat!

Mimiroon is saddened with
much sadness! Sad!

You lot look like you've
been to the seventh hell and
back. Report!

We discovered what we
thought were the remains
of imperial warmachina.

It came to life and started
tracking us. We cannot
return to Ala Ghiri without
putting the camp in danger!

Then that leaves us
but one option.

We must stop it, or at least
slow it down till reinforce-
ments arrive!

Awaiting bit deployment authorization......
Authorization granted.

Awaiting slasher deployment authorization......
Authorization granted.

Target locked on.
Initiating eradication protocol...
White flame, reduce all to ash!
A storm of swords and spells!
Yet not once did you show any sssign of fear.
Long have I desired to face one sssuch as you.
Hero of the wessst, I yield!

I have ssseen enough.
My thanksss, traveler.

What a finish! My sisters
will want to hear of this!

Do not feel bad. She is
their champion and all.

There is not a knight in all
the See who hasn't heard of
 's heroism...

Or who does not dream of
testing his mettle against
herhim.

Are you suggesting what I
think you're suggesting?

Oh most glorious of
glorious days!
Hide! I shall deal with these.

It cannot end here...
I must protect my charge...

What do you think's
wrong with the fry?

J'najaq Sunflare will not
leave this realm a coward!

Aye, young one. Would that
there were a single brave
soul on this whole isle...

You could always look for
shells with me.

I could, but shells will not
see me the greatest
bladesman in Hingashi.

I am Senban Oneblade.
You will find honor in
defeat at mine hands!

THERE!
THE GAP AT HIS FLANK!

But I am not
finished with you yet!

Well done, ijin.
I daresay you fight with
the heart of a Hingan.

Hmph. Perhaps the rumors I
heard of Eorzean mettle
were exaggerated.

That was more fun than
collecting shells!

Where is he!?
Where is Senban Oneblade!?

And I shall not
leave without it!

Who in the seven hells
are you, Redback?
Out the mouth of babes, eh?

What manner of craven dares
threaten a mere child!?

An honorable man would
allow you to tend to your
wounds, but I am no man, and
I care little for honor. Attack!

My thanks. You have shown
me honor is no stranger
to your people.

I shall remember this always.
Farewell. The mountains of
my homeland await.

I made no such promise!
But...I may have some time
before my ship sails.

Hey! You said we'd look
for shells when you finished!

I will return, Oneblade!
I. Will. Return!

Victory is mine!
Inform the bards that Senban
is now the Noneblade!

Once again, you have
my thanks for seeing
my sister safe.

You are well versed in
the art of war, it appears.

As it happens, my tribe
seeks a warrior of your
prowess to rid the land
of a terrible blight.

Its name is Humbaba, and
even the mighty J'moldva
could not stand against it.

If you are willing, I shall lead
you to its lair...and to glory
everlasting!

Today the blight shall end!
Today my sisters will be free!

The tribe will ever sing of
your deeds Your name will
echo in our hearts.

Come! There is no dishonor
in fleeing to fight again
another day.
Time for a song, I reckon!

STAB HIM IN THE
SOFT OF THE BELLY!

Heheh. You're not such a
tough guy after all.

I have done you a great
dishonor in underestimating
your ability, stranger. I shall
do so no longer!

Perhaps that mouth needs a
proper washing...with blood!

First koja, now
my own brothers!?

You will rue the day that
you raised your blade to
an innocent maid.

I've slain bigger creatures
than you, but none as foul!

Why does this always...always...
always always always
ALWAYS HAPPEN TO ME!!!?

YOU WANT SOME FISH!?
I'LL GIVE YOU SOME FISH!

I'LL RAM THIS FISH SO FAR
UP YOURGRSBRGYRGAAAH!

Feed the bull
his bleedin' bollocks!

Piss on the Twelve
and their bloody blessings!

Heh heh! The plunder's
right as rain!

Good! Then you can give
back to me and we'll all
stay friends!

Find you? It was your stink.
It carries across the entire
Ruby Sea.

And here I just had dip in
the springs last new moon!

Enough of this. Stand aside,
and we'll take back what's
rightfully ours. Or...

...we can kill you and take
it anyway. Forward, march!

Well, bollocks. Looks like me
charm wore off. Ye wouldn't
be mindin' another brawl now,
would ye?

Wh-What happened?
Where are we? Who are you?

My fish... My beautiful
fish... They're all...all...
all burnt to a crisp!
I can't eat them like this!

I guess I'll just have to
head back down to the
river and catch some more!

May the Matron show
us favor this day...
It's going to be a long day...
Scorpion 'round the bend! Remember to attack while it's tail's up!
We are the spear of the Fury and the shield of our brothers! Who are we!?
We have to hold them here!
Allow me to clear the way!

Courage and strength!
We will prevail!

I don't ever want to have
to do that again...
O Halone, see us to victory! Grant me the strength to strike down this foul creature!
A sad, sad day, this is. Sad!

Don't think you can get
away with this!
I saw that! I saw that!

I'm going to tell
your mothers!

The filthy duck ate
my favorite dzo!
And I fear I'll be next!

Bested...by a giant...duck...
I shall never live this down...

The skies will never be
safe as long as that duck
lives...

Something's emerged from
Bardam's Mettle...and it looks
hungry!

There's no time to move the
herd. We'll need to slow the
beast somehow!

If you haven't the will to
fight, you'd best run now!

There was no
way to stop it...

Ah! And now it's
heading for the pens!

You've saved us, traveler.
May the sun bless you.

How dare they...attack...
one of theirs... <pant> <pant>

Very well then. If I must spill
the blood of mine own kin...

We can be civil
about this, Gaei!

Just give us back the
coin we stole...plus, say,
another sack and we'll
call things even!

Keep your eyes peeled.
They may come at any moment.
Turned tail and ran like the dogs they are, I wager.
Thanks! Ye didn't bring a bite to yaffle on, did ye?
Y-You! Where did you come from!?
Ahaha! Oboro the Dim strikes again!

You're a dead man, Gaei!
A dead man hiding!

Do not think this is the end,
Confederate! The Red will see
our treasures back in our halls
and your heads on the walls!

I am in your debt, traveler!
Now pray keep me alive
so I can pay it!

Aye, I am here, my brothers!
And no, there will be no
compromise!

You will pay for what you
have done...with your lives!
I was hoping you'd say that.

Now's our chance! Follow
me if ye be keen on livin'!

Ye see, I've meself
a bonny of a plan!

It appears you've run
yourselves aground!

I expect as much from a
rum-soaked Confederate
but I'd heard you Westerners
were of a more clever stock.

Who ye calling rum-soaked?
I haven't had a drop in six
bells, no thanks to you!

We'll be sippin' grog out this
Red bastard's skull come
supper, like!

No matter. We will have what
is ours, and paint our shells
in your blood!

There be too godsdamned
many of them!

Break their spirits
and their backs!

Hah hah hah! Naught better
than a turtle on his back!

Me thanks, matey. Ye'd make
a fine Confederate, ye would!

Just wait! You will soon wish
you had died here today!

What have you gotten
yourself into this time!?

The thieves found me, and
would have killed me, had it
not been for this stranger.
I'd like to see them try!
So that's how it is, eh!?

I'll tear each and every one
of you from crotch to chin!

Go back to your own lands,
Eorzean. This is not your fight!

I will not quit until
justice is had!

How ever will we
survive the winter now...?

I'd tear their shells off...
...iffin' I had a leg to stand on.

More Redbacks comin'
o'er the ridge!

And I was lookin' forward
to drinkin' from that one's skull.

The sounds of battle have
faded. Have I come too late?
That was the last of them.

At least without my sword
I'm lighter on my feet...

What is important
is that you came.

I thought you said
that was the last of them!

Our fallen brothers will
bother us no longer.

Let them think
they have won...
Is this the one needs killing?
Go on! I'll not be long!

You've got something
to say to me, say it!

That's what I thought!
Now out of my way!

I've no quarrel with you,
outlander. But interfere
and I will take you down, too.

You should stick
to the gambling tents.

Are there none here who
might serve to right a wrong?

You have done the Blues a
great service. May you be
blessed.

Our altars will remain empty...
But not as empty as our hearts.

I believe I saw one over
near those rocks!

I must return home soon
to prepare the altars.

Still nothing to say, eh?
Let our fists do the
talking then!

That supposed to
be a thank you?
Right. I'll take that as a yes.

That'll learn me to
help a damn mute.

I don't want
to be a Budugan!

I wasn't born to fight!
I was born to herd!

You! Take your hands
off our new brother or
we'll cut them off!

Find her or it's your blood
I use in the next ritual!

She's a fox, not an eagle!
She could not have gone far!

You know not what
you do, stranger!
You will not stand in our way!

I must away...
Tamamo Gozen awaits...
No... Why must they do this!?

This kindness will
not be forgotten.

I must go now to my mistress.
Farewell, kind traveler.

The people... I must...
protect...the people...
What is this place? What binds me here?
Aaah! It feels as if my head were about to burst!
What is it that ails you, milady? Perhaps my associates and I can offer you succor.
So much dark... So much pain...
Did you feel that!? It was her! She is in there!
Kyubi of the Nine Tails! If you will not come out willingly, the girl's life is forfeit. Do you want that!?
Away! All of you. Only death awaits you here...
Your death, yes. And then your power will be ours!
Forget the ropes. We complete the ritual here!
Rise, my pet! It is time to feed!
Please... Run now... While I am still...myself...
I cannot hold on much lon─AAAAAAHHHHHH!!!
<growl> Who!? Who dares defile the land with their impure magicks!?
Brothers, behold! Protectress of Doma, Kyubi of the Nine Tails!

There! My mistress!
She is still here with us!

We must find her
before it is too late!
She is beyond my power. I must summon him.
Run, wicked defilers! I have eyes everywhere!
But my past... It remains veiled in shadow...
Kyubi of the Nine Tails! For twenty and five long summers have you wandered the land─
The wounds suffered in defense of your mortal charges deep as the abyss!
But today, that journey ends! By mine hand, I shall free you!
I shall free all of you!
Son of man! You are nothing!
No man may command me... No man but─
The spell of binding... Hurry! We must kill her! Now!
She is lost in her own mind!

We must lure her back,
or she'll be lost forever!

She must be saved, or
the land will be ever cursed!
FREE ME! FREE ME FROM THIS PAIN!
No. Her heart. It still beats!

Come then! We must
see her back to health!

Move your feet. You are
a Budugan now, boy!
They must have gone to ground, but where...

There has to be a clue
somewhere around here...

“Giant” my arse...
That thing is enormous!
Our spears will only anger it!
Men! We have something special for you today!
And some of you might just come out of it alive!
I'm not finished with you yet!

Azim! Why have
you forsaken us!

This wound will have to
be cleaned and dressed...
The wind is calm. The air clear.

Aye, the sun sends
us his blessing.

North. Past the Dawn Throne
and across Tao Khaal.
I shall ride at the van.

Anarba! That is not
for you to decide! Anarba!

They've our scent.
There'll be no outrunning
them now. Blades out!

Let us hope
that is all of them.

Our fortunes will turn...
We must will them so.

Rise, my people!
Our journey continues!
It is here we shall make camp!

The losses do not
seem too great... Still...

Gather, little ones!
It is time for milking!

Would the traveler
like to join me?

Rarely do we collect enough
to make cheese, but today...

So many jugs!
This calls for celebration!

Barely enough to boil a goat's
head. But it will have to do.

There! You can see the
dust rise from the steppe!

Even a few of their number
will fill our tribe's bellies
and see our tents warm.

A bowl of hot khorkhog
is reward enough for
the day's hunt!

The khorkhog will be thin
tonight, I'm afraid...

Quick, Altani!
See to the sheep!

It is the same pack that
hounded us earlier. They
will follow until they are
sated...or dead.
They will disturb us no longer.

Their noses are bloodied,
but if we do not leave now,
they will soon grow bold again.
